		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Simon]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sun, 18 Jan 2015 17:09:56 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://jamesclear-com.uar9g7bv-liquidwebsites.com/?p=6834#comment-14131</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[James, 

Great article as ever. However I disagree with your comment about criticism of science. Criticism is a very important part of the scientific process. Good science is subject to criticism at all stages of the process, from conception of the idea, planning of the experiment, competing for funding, data analysis and interpretation, writing of the manuscript, and finally editorial review. Rigorous criticism gives the consumer of science some measure of confidence in its quality.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>James, </p>
<p>Great article as ever. However I disagree with your comment about criticism of science. Criticism is a very important part of the scientific process. Good science is subject to criticism at all stages of the process, from conception of the idea, planning of the experiment, competing for funding, data analysis and interpretation, writing of the manuscript, and finally editorial review. Rigorous criticism gives the consumer of science some measure of confidence in its quality.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
