		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Joy Beer]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sat, 17 Jan 2015 17:12:08 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://jamesclear-com.uar9g7bv-liquidwebsites.com/?p=6834#comment-14127</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jamesclear.com/joseph-brodsky#comment-14107&quot;&gt;Paul&lt;/a&gt;.

I know exactly what you&#039;re getting at, as I thought of whistleblowers shedding light on evildoers, and therefore successfully shutting it down.  

Looking at the context of Brodsky&#039;s particular words above, though, I think he was taking what he learned about oppressors, and what he learned about returning to life again, to address graduating college kids.  Since he was telling them explicitly how to deal with the more (likely) negative characters in their upcoming lives, how not to let them steal space in one&#039;s brain, I think he really was teaching what James Clear is indicating he was.  I&#039;m pretty sure he was not preparing them all to deal with a superpower, but how to LIVE after having been oppressed and lost something.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://jamesclear.com/joseph-brodsky#comment-14107">Paul</a>.</p>
<p>I know exactly what you&#8217;re getting at, as I thought of whistleblowers shedding light on evildoers, and therefore successfully shutting it down.  </p>
<p>Looking at the context of Brodsky&#8217;s particular words above, though, I think he was taking what he learned about oppressors, and what he learned about returning to life again, to address graduating college kids.  Since he was telling them explicitly how to deal with the more (likely) negative characters in their upcoming lives, how not to let them steal space in one&#8217;s brain, I think he really was teaching what James Clear is indicating he was.  I&#8217;m pretty sure he was not preparing them all to deal with a superpower, but how to LIVE after having been oppressed and lost something.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
